    <note>Huang(2) Cishan [15449] His great grandson, Siyong [15465], was a Linchuan county resident, whose ancestors had moved from Fengcheng county. Since Lu You's funerary inscription for Cishan's son-in-law, Cheng(1) Hongji [15444], referes to him as a Linchuan person, I assume that the move (and segementation) took place with Cishan. In Lu You's funerary inscription, Cishan is identified by his zi, Jicen. Cishan was originally designated the #1 graduate, but because he used the taboo character of his lineage uncle (zufu), Huang Tingjian [7111], he was placed #4. His wenji is listed in CBD's bibliography and in SKQSZB, Vol. 4, p. 3295, under his alternate mingzi, Yanping and is so listed in the bibliography to this dataset. He was the #2 son of Huang(2) Deli according to the SKQSZM. CBD, 4, 2891.</note>
